Subject: Re: RSA - s/w sol. on 8-bit uP

In article <WARLORD.94Apr22203230@toxicwaste.mit.edu> warlord@MIT.EDU (Derek Atkins) writes:
>There was an article in Dr. Dobbs Journal, written by Burt Kaliski
>(sorry if I mispelled that, Burt) of RSADSI, which is an optimised
>modmult for 8-bit architecture.  It was printed last summer, and it
>includes code (I think 8080 assembly, or somthing like that).

It was the Z80180 The article describes operand and product scanning,
montgomery multiplication and some other tricks he used to get
the performance on the Z80180 to be reasonable. It was in the
September 1993 issue. 

Mark

